desc: Howdy! I'm a Computer Science Major in the class of '26 and I'm looking to get a masters degree and specialize in ML. In my free time I enjoy sleeping.

I am THE loudest and proudest member of the class of 2026 and I'm currently pursuing a bachelors degree in electrical engineering. I plan to work in infrastructure design, having previously interned at Burns & McDonnell and at HW Lochner, where I was a part of the team that oversaw the DFW Airport Way-finding Project. In addition to my work at TAO, I serve as the President and Station Manager of KANM Student Radio at Texas A&M University.
